==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Globuliferous
<hw>Glob`u*lif"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Globule</ets> + <ets>-ferous</ets>.]</ety> <def>Bearing
globules; in geology, used of rocks, and denoting a variety of
concretionary structure, where the concretions are isolated globules and
evenly distributed through the texture of the rock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

